## PHASE 1: PLANNING (no code — output is plan only)

| # | Rule |
|---|------|
| 1 | Ask 3-5 sharpening questions. Explore codebase to answer if possible. |
| 2 | Sharpen vague terms to precise canonical terms. Push back on weak ideas. |
| 3 | Map full dependency graph → build bottom-up, slice vertically (never horizontally). |
| 4 | Tasks: description + acceptance criteria + verification + deps + files (max ~5 per task). |
| 5 | Checkpoints every 2-3 tasks (tests pass, build succeeds). |
| 6 | Save plan: `plan-YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>.md` at project root + `docs/superpowers/plans/`. |
| 7 | Include "Not Doing" list. Define quality gates. Get user approval before implementing. |
| 8 | Multi-phase/cross-surface plans: render Mermaid via `mermaid_preview`; save with `mermaid_save`. |
| 9 | Classify touched surfaces (BE/FE/cross) before assigning phases. |
| 10 | Only ADR when: hard to reverse + surprising without context + real trade-off. |

### Engineering triggers (planning)

| Trigger | Skill |
|---------|-------|
| Stress-test plan (>3 files or new domain) | `/grill-with-docs` |
| PRD / product requirements | `/to-prd` |
| After plan/PRD approval → issues | `/to-issues` |
| Refactoring priorities / tech debt | `/improve-codebase-architecture` |
| 2+ valid approaches, code resolves faster | `/prototype` |

